

AI-Powered Phishing Detection System using Transformers

Overview
This is a production-ready AI system designed to detect phishing emails using deep learning and transformer-based NLP models. The system combines BiLSTM models (with GloVe and Word2Vec embeddings) and a DistilBERT transformer using a weighted ensemble approach to achieve high accuracy, robustness, and real-time inference.

It is built with a focus on real-world deployment, cybersecurity applications, and scalable AI systems.

---

Problem Statement
Traditional email filtering systems struggle to detect modern phishing attacks. These attacks often involve obfuscated content, context-aware manipulation, and zero-day threats that bypass rule-based systems.

This system solves the problem using context-aware AI models that understand semantic and linguistic patterns rather than relying on static keyword matching.

---

Core Features

* Transformer-based NLP using DistilBERT
* BiLSTM models with Word2Vec and GloVe embeddings
* Ensemble learning for improved accuracy and robustness
* Real-time phishing detection
* Batch email analysis using CSV input
* Web-based interface built with Flask
* Threshold tuning to balance precision and recall
* Stateless architecture with no database dependency

---

System Architecture
Input email is first passed through a preprocessing pipeline where text cleaning, masking, and tokenization are applied.
The processed data is then fed into three models: GloVe BiLSTM, Word2Vec BiLSTM, and DistilBERT.
Outputs from these models are combined using a weighted ensemble to produce the final classification as phishing or legitimate.

---

