Performance Notes
DistilBERT is used instead of BERT for faster inference and reduced memory usage.
The ensemble approach improves robustness across diverse phishing patterns.
Threshold tuning is applied to balance precision and recall effectively.
The system is optimized for low-latency real-time predictions.

---

Key Engineering Decisions
DistilBERT was chosen over BERT to achieve faster inference with minimal accuracy loss.
Combining BiLSTM with Transformers allows capturing both sequential and contextual features.
Weighted ensemble reduces model bias and improves overall detection performance.
Stateless architecture simplifies deployment and scaling in production environments.

